art of the biologically determined family. In addition to illuminating the roles and experiences of these figures, \u003cI\u003eAll in the Family\u003c\/I\u003e reveals how this social network was integrated into the family both in practice and in ideology, presenting a more complex view of the Roman family than the traditional nuclear structure. \u003cbr\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://doi.org/10.3998/mpub.12705608\"\u003eView on Fulcrum platform.\u003c\/a\u003e\u003c\/div\u003e","identifier":"https://doi.org/10.3998/mpub.12705608","language":"eng","modified":"2025-08-16T08:24:14Z","published":"2025-01-01","publisher":"University of Michigan Press","subject":["Classical Studies:Roman","Anthropology:Cultural Anthropology","History:Historical Methods and Theory"]},"links":[{"rel":"self","href":"https://www.fulcrum.org/ebooks/ww72bf691/download","type":"application/epub+zip"},{"rel":"http://opds-spec.org/acquisition/open-access","href":"https://www.fulcrum.org/ebooks/ww72bf691/download","type":"application/epub+zip"},{"rel":"http://opds-spec.org/acquisition/open-access","href":"https://www.fulcrum.org/ebooks/000003050/download","type":"application/pdf"}],"images":[{"href":"https://www.fulcrum.org//image-service/t435gh29k/full/full/0/default.jpg","type":"image/jpeg"},{"href":"https://www.fulcrum.org//image-service/t435gh29k/full/200,/0/default.jpg","width":200,"type":"image/jpeg"},{"href":"https://www.fulcrum.org//image-service/t435gh29k/full/400,/0/default.jpg","width":400,"type":"image/jpeg"},{"href":"https://www.fulcrum.org//image-service/t435gh29k/full/800,/0/default.jpg","width":800,"type":"image/jpeg"}]},{"metadata":{"@type":"http://schema.org/EBook","title":"Mountain Wolf Woman, Sister of Crashing Thunder: The Autobiography of a Winnebago Indian","author":"Lurie, Nancy Oestreich","belongsTo":{"series":"Ann Arbor Paperbacks"},"description":"\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cP\u003e From pony to airplane, from medicine dance to Christian worship, \u003cI\u003eMountain Wolf Woman, 