eformers to engage closely with these genres. Yu became a vocal advocate of teaching with moral vernacular literature that he believed met commoners at their level. He emphasized the hope that by writing, printing, and performing such texts, every member of his audience could be transformed into teachers themselves, restoring society from the bottom up.\u003cbr\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://doi.org/10.3998/mpub.14428723\"\u003eView on Fulcrum platform.\u003c\/a\u003e\u003c\/div\u003e","identifier":"https://doi.org/10.3998/mpub.14428723","language":"eng","modified":"2025-08-27T08:22:05Z","published":"2025-01-01","publisher":"University of Michigan Press","subject":["Literary Studies:Asian Literature","Asian Studies:China"]},"links":[{"rel":"self","href":"https://www.fulcrum.org/ebooks/0v838398b/download","type":"application/epub+zip"},{"rel":"http://opds-spec.org/acquisition/open-access","href":"https://www.fulcrum.org/ebooks/0v838398b/download","type":"application/epub+zip"},{"rel":"http://opds-spec.org/acquisition/open-access","href":"https://www.fulcrum.org/ebooks/rx913s883/download","type":"application/pdf"}],"images":[{"href":"https://www.fulcrum.org//image-service/2n49t480x/full/full/0/default.jpg","type":"image/jpeg"},{"href":"https://www.fulcrum.org//image-service/2n49t480x/full/200,/0/default.jpg","width":200,"type":"image/jpeg"},{"href":"https://www.fulcrum.org//image-service/2n49t480x/full/400,/0/default.jpg","width":400,"type":"image/jpeg"},{"href":"https://www.fulcrum.org//image-service/2n49t480x/full/800,/0/default.jpg","width":800,"type":"image/jpeg"}]},{"metadata":{"@type":"http://schema.org/EBook","title":"Cultural Production of Hallyu in the Digital Platform Era: Industry Perspectives","author":"Jin, Dal Yong","description":"\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cI\u003eCultural Production of Hallyu in the Digital Platform Era \u003c\/I\u003eexplores how histories, industry structures, and politics interact in the platformization of the Korean Wave. Dal Yong Jin argues