gins, showing that IR witnessed a sharp turn to \u003cI\u003etheoretical \u003c\/I\u003econsideration of international politics beginning around 1950, and remained preoccupied with theory. Taking place in 1953–54, the CFR study group represents a vital snapshot of this shift.\u003c\/P\u003e\u003cP\u003eThis book situates the CFR study group in its historical and historiographical contexts, and offers a biographical analysis of the participants. It includes seven preparatory papers on diverse theoretical approaches, penned by former Berkeley political scientist George A. Lipsky, followed by the digest of discussions from the study group meetings. \u003cI\u003eAmerican Power and International Theory at the Council on Foreign Relations, 1953–54 \u003c\/I\u003eoffers new insights into the early development of IR as well as the thinking of prominent elites in the early years of the Cold War.\u003c\/P\u003e \u003cbr\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://doi.org/10.3998/mpub.11301034\"\u003eView on Fulcrum platform.\u003c\/a\u003e\u003c\/div\u003e","identifier":"https://doi.org/10.3998/mpub.11301034","language":"eng","modified":"2025-07-20T08:24:00Z","published":"2020-01-01","publisher":"University of Michigan Press","subject":"Political Science:International Relations"},"links":[{"rel":"self","href":"https://www.fulcrum.org/ebooks/cz30pv139/download","type":"application/epub+zip"},{"rel":"http://opds-spec.org/acquisition/open-access","href":"https://www.fulcrum.org/ebooks/cz30pv139/download","type":"application/epub+zip"},{"rel":"http://opds-spec.org/acquisition/open-access","href":"https://www.fulcrum.org/ebooks/vm40xt268/download","type":"application/pdf"}],"images":[{"href":"https://www.fulcrum.org//image-service/ww72bd15h/full/full/0/default.jpg","type":"image/jpeg"},{"href":"https://www.fulcrum.org//image-service/ww72bd15h/full/200,/0/default.jpg","width":200,"type":"image/jpeg"},{"href":"https://www.fulcrum.org//image-service/ww72bd15h/full/400,/0/default.jpg","width":400,"ty