s. The individuals whose stories are reevaluated include German Jews Ernst Lubitsch, David Einhorn, and Gershom Scholem, the architect Fritz Nathan and filmmaker Helmar Lerski; and eastern European Jews David Bergelson, Der Nister, Jacob Katz, Joseph Soloveitchik, and Abraham Joshua Heschel—figures not normally associated with Germany. \u003cI\u003eThree-Way Street\u003c\/I\u003e addresses the gap in the scholarly literature as it opens up critical ways of approaching Jewish culture not only in Germany, but also in other locations, from the mid-nineteenth century to the present.\u003cBR /\u003e\u003cBR /\u003e  \u003c\/DIV\u003e\u003cBR /\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://doi.org/10.3998/mpub.9221214\"\u003eView on Fulcrum platform.\u003c\/a\u003e\u003c\/div\u003e","identifier":"https://doi.org/10.3998/mpub.9221214","language":"eng","modified":"2025-07-20T08:22:42Z","published":"2016-01-01","publisher":"University of Michigan Press","subject":["German Studies","Cultural Studies","History","Jewish Studies"]},"links":[{"rel":"self","href":"https://www.fulcrum.org/ebooks/0k225b94v/download","type":"application/epub+zip"},{"rel":"http://opds-spec.org/acquisition/open-access","href":"https://www.fulcrum.org/ebooks/0k225b94v/download","type":"application/epub+zip"},{"rel":"http://opds-spec.org/acquisition/open-access","href":"https://www.fulcrum.org/ebooks/2z10wr357/download","type":"application/pdf"}],"images":[{"href":"https://www.fulcrum.org//image-service/2801ph18r/full/full/0/default.jpg","type":"image/jpeg"},{"href":"https://www.fulcrum.org//image-service/2801ph18r/full/200,/0/default.jpg","width":200,"type":"image/jpeg"},{"href":"https://www.fulcrum.org//image-service/2801ph18r/full/400,/0/default.jpg","width":400,"type":"image/jpeg"},{"href":"https://www.fulcrum.org//image-service/2801ph18r/full/800,/0/default.jpg","width":800,"type":"image/jpeg"}]},{"metadata":{"@type":"http://schema.org/EBook","title":"European-Russian Power Relations in Turbulent Times"