 in terms of intersubjectivity and validity. Drawing upon Kantian aesthetic theory as well as case law, legal theory, and constitutional theory, Edlin develops a new conceptual framework for the respective roles of the individual judge and of the judiciary as an institution, as well as the relationship between them, as integral parts of the broader legal and political community. Specifically, Edlin situates a judge\u0026#39;s subjective responses within a form of legal reasoning and reflective judgment that must be communicated to different audiences.\u003cBR /\u003e\u003cBR /\u003e Edlin concludes that the individual values and perspectives of judges are indispensable both to their judgments in specific cases and to the independence of the courts. According to the common law tradition, judicial subjectivity is a virtue, not a vice.\u003c\/DIV\u003e\u003cBR /\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://doi.org/10.3998/mpub.3783964\"\u003eView on Fulcrum platform.\u003c\/a\u003e\u003c\/div\u003e","identifier":"https://doi.org/10.3998/mpub.3783964","language":"eng","modified":"2025-07-19T09:08:49Z","published":"2016-01-01","publisher":"University of Michigan Press","subject":["Law:Supreme Court and Constitutional Law","Law:Comparative Law","Political Science:Judicial Politics","Law:Law and Society"]},"links":[{"rel":"self","href":"https://www.fulcrum.org/ebooks/9g54xj54m/download","type":"application/epub+zip"},{"rel":"http://opds-spec.org/acquisition/open-access","href":"https://www.fulcrum.org/ebooks/9g54xj54m/download","type":"application/epub+zip"},{"rel":"http://opds-spec.org/acquisition/open-access","href":"https://www.fulcrum.org/ebooks/pv63g158g/download","type":"application/pdf"}],"images":[{"href":"https://www.fulcrum.org//image-service/s7526d423/full/full/0/default.jpg","type":"image/jpeg"},{"href":"https://www.fulcrum.org//image-service/s7526d423/full/200,/0/default.jpg","width":200,"type":"image/jpeg"},{"href":"https://www.fulcrum.org//image-service/s7526d4